a-target=\"#ZdExportPDFModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2525836\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2525836\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104aqs1665702566840.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/aqs1665702566840.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/aqs1665702566840.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"aqs1665702566840\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Uniface-Compliant Attribute Declarations\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface supports a subset of the attribute declarations that are available in the XML standard, namely declarations for attributes for processing information, and declarations for namespaces.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"aqs1665702566840__p_d38654e1_d38655e1_d38656e1\">You can use the following attribute declarations in your DTDs:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"aqs1665702566840__li_d19544e1_d19545e1_d19546e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;!ATTLIST</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">EntityElement</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">id</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">CDATA #REQUIRED&gt;</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"aqs1665702566840__li_d19547e1_d19548e1_d19549e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;!ATTLIST</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">EntityElement</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">crc</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">CDATA #REQUIRED&gt;</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"aqs1665702566840__li_d19550e1_d19551e1_d19552e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;!ATTLIST</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">EntityElement</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">status</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">CDATA #REQUIRED&gt;</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"aqs1665702566840__li_d19553e1_d19554e1_d19555e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;!ATTLIST</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">EntityElement</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">valerr CDATA #IMPLIED&gt;</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"aqs1665702566840__li_d19556e1_d19557e1_d19558e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;!ATTLIST</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">FieldElement</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">valerr CDATA #IMPLIED&gt;</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"aqs1665702566840__li_d19559e1_d19560e1_d19561e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;!ATTLIST</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ElementName</var>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">AttributeName</var> \"<var class=\"keyword varname\">AttributeValue</var>\" <code class=\"ph codeph\">#FIXED&gt;</code>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\">where:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"aqs1665702566840__li_d19562e1_d19563e1_d19564e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">EntityElement</var>—name of an element mapped to a Uniface entity\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"aqs1665702566840__li_d19565e1_d19566e1_d19567e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">FieldElement</var>—name of an element mapped to a Uniface field\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"aqs1665702566840__li_d19568e1_d19569e1_d19570e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ElementName</var>—<var class=\"keyword varname\">EntityElement</var> or <var class=\"keyword varname\">FieldElement</var>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"aqs1665702566840__li_d19571e1_d19572e1_d19573e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">AttributeName</var>—name of the attribute\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"aqs1665702566840__li_d19574e1_d19575e1_d19576e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">AttributeValue</var>—value of the attribute\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"aqs1665702566840__p_d38657e1_d38658e1_d38659e1\">Use <code class=\"ph codeph\">#FIXED</code> attributes to declare namespaces for your XML element names.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"aqs1665702566840__section_fbm_5hz_pcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1211643e194\">XML Standard Syntax</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"aqs1665702566840__p_d38663e1_d38664e1_d38665e1\">For comparison purposes, see the syntax for attribute\n            declarations in <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xzq1665702699858.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xzq1665702699858.html\" title=\"The XML ATTLIST declaration defines the attributes that an XML element can have.\">XML Attribute Declaration</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"aqs1665702566840__p_d38666e1_d38667e1_d38668e1\">The XML standard also allows an alternative syntax for\n            attribute declarations, whereby all attributes are declared for an element in one\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;!ATTLIST&gt;</code> declaration. This syntax is not supported for\n            Uniface XML streams.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sua1665702566764.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Attributes in Uniface XML Streams</a><p>Uniface uses attributes in XML streams to store data processing information and to define custom attributes.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uab1665702654218.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface-Compliant DTDs</a><p>A Document Type Definition (DTD) defines rules for the structure of an XML stream. In Uniface, a DTD is a development object that includes DTD definitions and a default mapping between the XML elements defined by the DTD and Uniface component fields and entities. It can be used to define the rules for the structure of an XML stream that is exchanged between components.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525836\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525836\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface-Compliant Attribute Declarations Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface-Compliant Attribute Declarations Uniface supports a subset of the attribute declarations that are available in the XML standard, namely declarations for attributes for processing information, and declarations for namespaces. You can use the following attribute declarations in your DTDs: <!ATTLIST EntityElement id CDATA #REQUIRED> <!ATTLIST EntityElement crc CDATA #REQUIRED> <!ATTLIST EntityElement status CDATA #REQUIRED> <!ATTLIST EntityElement valerr CDATA #IMPLIED> <!ATTLIST FieldElement valerr CDATA #IMPLIED> <!ATTLIST ElementName AttributeName \" AttributeValue \" #FIXED> where: EntityElement —name of an element mapped to a Uniface entity FieldElement —name of an element mapped to a Uniface field ElementName — EntityElement or FieldElement AttributeName —name of the attribute AttributeValue —value of the attribute Use #FIXED attributes to declare namespaces for your XML element names. XML Standard Syntax For comparison purposes, see the syntax for attribute declarations in XML Attribute Declaration . The XML standard also allows an alternative syntax for attribute declarations, whereby all attributes are declared for an element in one <!ATTLIST> declaration. This syntax is not supported for Uniface XML streams. Related Links Attributes in Uniface XML Streams Uniface uses attributes in XML streams to store data processing information and to define custom attributes. Uniface-Compliant DTDs A Document Type Definition (DTD) defines rules for the structure of an XML stream. In Uniface, a DTD is a development object that includes DTD definitions and a default mapping between the XML elements defined by the DTD and Uniface component fields and entities. It can be used to define the rules for the structure of an XML stream that is exchanged between components. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}